*Spolier alert*
I saw the ratings on a few sites and I bet they were all done by people in their early 20's lol.. people that have no connection to the originals like we late 20's / 30's do. I loved every minute of it and even found little things sad that normally I wouldnt have done in films. Thats because of the emotional connections we have to the programmes. The opening scene sucked me in straight away with the yellow ranger and Zordon dying.
I loved learning about these characters and their stories. We never got to see this side in the programmes.. they were just school kids and that's all we knew.
Loved that they made us wait untill near the end of the film before they morphed to show the togetherness they had to have. That's what made the morphing scene so good.. "It's morphing time" - Love when Jason said that. Could have had more passion though 😂. 
They connected the film to our day and age with an autistic character, bi / gay (?) character and someone that looks after his mum. Also showed Kimberly talking about the issues these days with people sending indecent pictures of themselves and Jason showed if you try hard there's always something else you can be good at going the american football to leading the Rangers.
The ratings it received were way too harsh. Too much action and it would have been just a kids film. They made it for us. Bring on part 2....

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment: I gotta say, this is the most underrated movie of all time in my list. After thinking it was gonna be just another Cheesy movie to the power ranger history of movies, I decided to give it a shot and for the first 10 min I was so hooked on this. Just watched it again with my fam cuz I was so happy with it and they thought it was going to be so cheesy but guess what, they loved it! The story and build up is what caught my eye. The casting was perfect. Fighting flawless. Soundtrack was Just magnificent. I honestly consider putting this somewhere in my top 20 or 30, and I’ve seen almost every movie made lol. I honestly hope they make a second one. Please ignore the reviews of how bad it was because this was a thriller for me. Great directing! This movie really touched me a few times and there were a few plot twists that caught me way off guard! (Cough cough train scene) Loved the movie :) now pls make a second one! (Btw I’m not a kid, I’m 20 yo)

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
Okay so before you watch this, there are some issues. This won't contain spoilers. First of all Power Rangers 2017 is nothing like gen 1 90's PR. This is actually a good thing, means it isn't super cheesy. Other good things include the fact that the baddies no longer double as comic relief. It's also a good movie which doesn't milk the past too much. 

Now the bad, and rising above all else is the fact that the rangers don't morph until the final 30 mins of the movie, which is just too late. There is little time, so we see 30 secs of fighting in armour before we jump straight to the zords. Speaking of the zords, the sped up final battle is so hectic that we don't really get time to see the zords. Really hoping there'll be a sequel, because if not then there's just too little ranger time in a movie supposedly made for fans. 

There is also the matter of American PC. Trini, the yellow ranger, can no longer be Asian, and the black ranger Zach cannot be black. Billy is now black, but still has the nerdy personality of white Billy cause we can't have a dancing and hip hop loving black ranger. 

I couldn't care less about the race changes, I'd be perfectly happy with a Samoan Jason as long as he played the part of Jason..... I just wish the reasons the changes were made weren't so painfully obvious.

The opening of the movie (ending with Rita falling into the sea) was my favorite part.
A serious prequel, set during the end of the Cretaceous Era (where this movie starts).

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
REVIEW, NO SPOILERS.

This movie was good at first, it wasn't as cliche as I thought it would be at the start. 
I mean, sure, you kinda have your cliche school children 'group', but that's what the original power rangers was like. 

Aside from the start - it became almost too predictable, oh, this is about to happen? Well, I know what'll happen next. It was literally like that, it was comedy more than anything. You're also dealing with too much cheesy story line, sure, the actors were okay with this type of movie but the story line was the huge problem. 
It was like watching Dora asking you where the most obvious thing is, yeah, it's that painful. 

I do believe they aimed this at the wrong audience, felt like for kids, but not for kids(?) I don't know what that's all about, the "Billy" of the group fitted in perfectly, and he was probably my favourite character of them all, because he fit in his role well and he did a good job with it. 
I'd give this movie a 4/10 and that's at a stretch, I would've gotten my money back if I could, obviously point of views are a thing w/ opinions, so don't take my word for it, look at other reviews and check out some clips to note your decision down compared to mine. 

Thanks.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
I remember seeing a commercial on TV for the pilot of series, when this show first came out the U.S. (I think that it was '93) and thinking "This show won't last more than a few episodes".
It just looked so AWEFUL.
The costumes and make-up for the villains were laughably cheap, the acting was WAY over the top (especially for the villains), the dialogue was cheesy beyond belief, and the girl rangers actually wore SKIRTS! When was the last time that you saw a female soldier wearing a skirt into combat?
It was like watching an extremely low budget 1950s/early 1960s Godzilla movie crossed with Plan 9 From Outer Space.
Which isn't to say that it couldn't have been great as an animated show.
Needless to say, I never watched the series; but this movie actually looks really good!
I've heard a lot of really good reviews about it; and they say that about the first 2/3rds of it consist of really good character-development.
Well, except for the part about one of the male Rangers briefly accidentally giving a bull a hand-job (apparently, he couldn't tell a male from a female).
I think that I'll go see it.

I liked this movie enough to actually want a sequel. Mostly because I want to see more fight scenes in their suits. Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment: this is a awesome movie. i was a little nervous going into this movie. i did not want the film makers to mess up my childhood show. but i was very impressed with the movie. they did not change too much, they did change the characteristics of some of the rangers but not too much the one that was portrayed very well was billy the blue ranger and rita was done very well as well. ok here are some spoilers do not continue to read if you don't want to know. one thing i really liked about it was that they did not know each other and you see the friendship grow, you get to see the bacground of the rangers and their personal lives. you see them meet for the first time and see the friendship grow, you see them train, having trouble morphing, using the zords and so on. they are not told by zordon on how to do stuff but learn on their own. u see the history of zordon and rita. you know how in the show they mention that zordon was a ranger well you see that in this movie. and there is some homage to the film like, it's morphing time, alpha says his catch phrase and when you see all the dino zords running in a montage the theme song plays. i was highly satisfied with this movie they changed it a little bit but kept true to what the power rangers are and the costumes were awesome. goldar was even cool. the acting was good, the story was good and the special effects are good. and the zords were sweet. can't wait for the sequel. make sure you watch after the credits. if you have not seen this movie then i recommend you do and the putties were well made as well rating 5/5

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
I had doubts about this movie when it first announced, and now I see why my gut had doubts. The first bad thing they did was give a release date with absolutely nothing to back it behind. Seriously, even Michael Bay wouldn't do something that stupid. The second stupid thing they did was hire Zack Stentz and Ashley Miller, the two writing hacks behind the Transformers and Star Trek films. I honestly think these two don't even bother researching the source material for the films they make, instead they just shit out whatever they come with. Because of them, the movie took WAY too many liberties to where the personalities of the characters don't match the real Power Ranger characters, nor does it match the real Power Rangers origin story. Yes, I can accept SOME changes to a new adaptation (I did that with the Chris Nolan Batman trilogy), but I can't accept characters who do something out of character. You've never seen Jason pranking a rival high school team then have the cops come after him, you've never seen any of the other rangers be portrayed as angsty (or "screw ups" as they call themselves), and you've never heard Zordon tell the rangers they're unworthy to be Power Rangers. FYI, I have nothing against the cast, because they can only work with what they're given, and that's not their fault. However, they could research the character they were portraying to help get into character. The next stupid thing they did was hire Dean Israelite as the director, even though most of his films are half-assed, because they often get 5 or 6 out of 10 stars (look up his directing credits on IMDB).

I'll admit I was excited to see this movie after watching this trailer, because it changed my views on if it would be good or not. It made me think that this would be not only a fresh take, but a good take, on the franchise. Now all of that excitement went down the shitter after seeing this piece of shit all of the way through on opening night. I walked out of that theater feeling insulted, and was shocked to realize what I saw was not a Power Rangers movie. Ever since I got home that night, and up until now, I've been getting my thoughts down on paper for a fan-film reboot as a way to make up for this film. I shouldn't have to reboot this "reboot", but no, Shat Stentz and Ass-ley Miller made me feel a need to do this, because like the typical leeches that they are, they clearly don't respect franchises like this one. And just so you're aware, this fan-film will have some changes as well, but it will still relate itself to the source material at the same time.

Comment:
Power Rangers (2017) is one of the prime examples of movies that are actually done better then what they should've been. It does have trouble living up to its namestake due to its inconsistent pacing and anticlimactic buildup, but the cast is astonishing, the action is good mindless fun and everything you would expect to be in a Power Rangers show or film (including that kick ass 1995 movie theme) is all there and accounted for, even with the change in tone. If you're a hardcore longtime Power Rangers fan, you'll definitely have a mighty morphin' good time with this one.


Verdict: 7/10

this movie is gonna be awesome, now before any of you haters start attacking me hear me out.

OK but seeing them in motion is a bigger difference than seeing them in a picture or poster. 4. all the characters so far seem to be really likable. 5. yes it's an unknown cast, but not all the cast is unknown and they really seem to care for the project and had lots of fun doing it.
that's all I had to say.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
Eh... 3 things are killing this for me.

1.) Kanye West. <SIGH> Lionsgate... If the same person that chose this song chose the same music for the Warcraft trailer, fire them. The music once again does not fit whatsoever.
2.) Goldar's redesign. His monster costume in the original was amazing. By far one of the best in the entire series. If it ain't broken, why fix it? (Thank God for the Rita redesign though.)
3.) Alpha 5 is now a sarcastic robot...? The humor with Alpha 5 is that it's suppose to freak out and be panicky. That's the joke.

I'll still see the movie regardless, but I felt the need to at least give some form of constructed criticism.

I don't like how this is turning out. Explicitly saying these are new rangers helps a little, but everything that can be compared with the old rangers looks awful. The Megazord is REALLY, REALLY BAD, Alpha is REALLY BAD, even the morpher. I can look at the related videos while typing this and see a fan video that has considerably simpler and better aesthetics from the thumbnail alone. Taking a look, it's that fan short from Bootleg Universe that made everyone want a Power Rangers movie in the first place. It's already better than this despite the assault rifles.

The effects look like those mindless Transformers movies, which attempt overstimulation just for the sake of catching eyes and what little I've learned about the Rangers' characters through reveals already makes them either extremely plain or unlikable.

This idea did not age with its target audience that is now in their twenties.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
As much as I liked the original power rangers as a kid, looking back, the show was always cheesy. The actors were dorky, the acting was hilarious, the enemies were silly, but the watching a bunch of normal teens kung fu-ing bad guys in colorful super spandex never got old and seeing megazord transform and fight was magical. I wasn't sold on the film before, but I feel like this trailer captures and updates a lot of what the original was about, and I only hope kids will enjoy it the way I did.

Let's not pretend the original show was an untouchable masterpiece and should not be remade. Aliens, or Robocop, or Terminator are classic films by masters that shouldn't be remade, but anyone thinking the same applies to Power Rangers is delusional.

Comment:
Man, I think I MIGHT actually like this. I mean, I remember hearing about this new show called "Power Rangers" as a kid and having my mind jump to a bunch of super powered park rangers, but then I saw that first episode and lost my mind.

 So I'm biased.

 But hey, it's all there; a group of five teenagers wind up with Zordon (and nightmare inducing Alpha 5), get turned into the power rangers, kick the crap out of some Puttys (decent martial arts too), Rita Repulsa makes her monster grow (couldn't resist), the Zords show up, actually DO something against Goldar (get their asses kicked it looks like), then form the Megazord, and doubtless kick the crap out of him. It's the first episode in big budget movie form, with a heavy lean on the alien angle.

I'm in. I was on the fence for a long time, but I'm in.

But Rita had BETTER come from a space-dumpster! (I kid)

Comment: I see comments of people not taking the reboot well. If you don't want to count it as canon, then don't. Just give the movie a fair chance. And in all reality, the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers are an alternation of the Super Sentai, the ORIGINAL series. Power Rangers is basically the Americanized version of it, because it's a live action show and dubbing is for animation. In all of the scenes where you see characters in the flesh, that's the reenactment, in the scenes where they're in their transformed states, it's dubbed to the suitable audience. That's my theory, at least. But back on topic, to those complaining that this movie will 'ruin their childhood', you don't have to count this movie as canon, as the original Power Rangers is basically a different continuity than the source material. Did you know that there's Super Sentai series BEFORE the one that was converted to MMPR that were never reenacted and dubbed?

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
Top wins shown so far:
1. Realistic armor and circuits in the suits give the Rangers more credibility. I would take those Rangers more seriously than the spandex wearing ones any day.
2. The fact that Rita appears in the Yellow Ranger's home shows that the Villains know the Rangers' true identities, providing an actual serious threat compared to the bumbling idiotic Rita in the original TV show.
3. All design complaints about the Zords aside, they are shown to fire actual ammunition compared to the typical 90s fantasy lasers in the original series. Again, bonus points for reality based weaponry.
4. Those Putties actually look like they are made out of rocks this time.
5. A bit of actual Zord piloting is shown to be done by the Rangers compared to the lazy "voice command" piloting style of the original Rangers. Always a win for the attention to detail.
-And that, folks, is why i have faith in this movie. Just my thoughts, take it easy.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment: Okay a lot of people are complaining about how different this looks compared to the original series.  And a lot of people are responding that those fans need to understand that changes have to happen.  That the show was cheesy and the characters were just bland stereotypes.  There is some truth to those statements I’m not denying that BUT this is just substituting one form of stereotype for another.  We’ve gone from five idealistic do-gooders to five angsty emos who look like they just came from Fan4stic.  Rita Repulsa is still the on-note world-conqueror just in a skimpy outfit.  Though the worst part are the zords and henchmen.  In the case of the former their redesign makes them look like Michael Bay’s Transformers.  And in the latter they’ve taken some fairly uniquely designed villains from the original like Goldar and the Putties and turned them into interchangeable generic monsters.  The crowning cherry of crap here though is the rap music.  Because the last time someone mixed rap with Power Rangers it worked so well.  The only update that seems to work is the revamped Zordon and the Ranger’s suits which look very impressive.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
Imagine if an adaptation we all love, say Game of Thrones or the Lord of the Rings films (which I understand have inaccuracies, but not enough to derail many fans of the original books) had as much in common with their original books as this trailer has in common with the original Power Rangers series. We would all be furious.

This looks like the writers or studio or whatever were told to make a Power Rangers film, so they read the first few pages of the wikipedia page and then wrote the script. Now matter what kind of reviews this movie ends up getting, it's shameful to call this a Power Rangers adaptation.

For fans of the old series looking for a more faithful modern adaptation, I would recommend the Power Rangers comics from Boom! studios. It has much of what we loved about the TV series, but is written well enough that adults who loved the series as kids can enjoy it.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment: The way I see it is, we still don't know 100% until the movie comes out. Anything can happen in the meantime. Reshoots, added or removed scenes, more time to perfect the special effects, and other marketing efforts. As for the Rangers, I personally saw much better interaction this time around compared to the 1st trailer. Not too happy with Alpha's design, and I wish they'd enhanced Zordon's voice to give it more ethereal, alienistic quality. Goldar's design doesnt look very original or amazing, and I wonder if he will retain any of his personality from the original show. Finally, I actually don't mind the Rangers having super powers, as I believe Dino Thunder actually did this with their Rangers (and fun tie in: Tommy, the original green ranger- and later on, gold ranger and red ranger- was in that season). So, who knows what else they're going to do with this. I'm nervous but at the same time the only thing I'll be losing is some time and money, as I still have the original series to go back to.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment: I already know exactly what the problem is gonna be with this whole film; it won't be the cgi, the story, or the acting. It's the fact that there won't be any tension. I figured it out as soon as I saw that one Ranger say "that's a lotta gold" at 1:58. If there's a giant supernatural monster killing people and destroying a town, are you going to be smiling and making jokes about it as it happens? No, you won't, especially if you're one of the people trying to save lives. They're throwing lines like that in out of nowhere in an effort to make seem like it a fun, quippy action blockbuster, but up until that point the film instead seemed like it was going to be a gritty real-world take on the Power Rangers story. I hope it's good, but this trailer lowered my expectations.

Comment:
EVERYTHING WRONG WITH THE POWER RANGERS TRAILER
A Cinema Sins rip-off

1. 0:00 - 0:04 Footage near the end of the trailer is at the beginning, signifying either an inaccurate circle of life theme or shitty editing. Given Hollywood's perception of the general movie going audience, I'm inclined toward the latter. +1

2. 0:06 The stop sign is too close to, and in full view of, the stop sign indicator, negating the yellow sign's purpose. +1

3. 0:08 - 0:10 Then what brought you together? Detention?  +1

Also, if you're merely acquaintances, then why are you ready to fuck around in a restricted area together? +1

 4. 0:11 - 0:13 Character telling other characters what they already know merely to inform the audience cliché. +1

5. 0:14 - 0:20 Not somehow. You broke into a restricted area together. +1

6. 0:24 - 0:27 That's not glowing; that's peeing in the pool. +1

Also, are they assigned their ranger colors by the coins they carry? Because this scene makes it look like it's by the color of their topmost outer garment. +1

7. 0:36 If she breaks her phone in this scene, then why does she ask the black guy how strong he is in the previous trailer? Scenes don't match up. Even if this scene takes place later on in the movie, it still doesn't work because they got their coins at the same time and should therefore be experiencing puberty--I-I mean their powers simultaneously. +1

8. 0:38 Thank you Captain Obvious. Your contribution is unquestionably beneficial. +1

9. 0:42 - 0:43 Angle of attack differs from angle of impact. +1

10. 0:51 Zordon is the PG-13 version of Pinhead. +1

11. 0:53 - 0:55 Obvious dialogue jump is obvious. +1

12. 0:56 - 0:57 No, you're talking to someone through a communicative device. +1

13. 0:57 - 0:59 So was I of your design. Who signed off on that thing? H. P. Lovecraft?  +1

14. 1:02 Where exactly is Angel Grove located? First it's a suburban area and now it's a mountainous region with a fishing community. +1

Also, If it's _not_ a fishing community, then this is a wealthy area whose residents love to go boating, which is hypocritical to the "weirdos and criminals" line from the previous trailer. +1

15. 1:04 - 1:10 Cute line, but there's no way she would actually say this to anyone in ear shot who hasn't experienced it, as they wouldn't believe her.

1:11 - 1:12 See? Now she's going to have to get a psychiatric evaluation and be watched like a hawk by her parents, thus preventing her from ever becoming a Power Ranger. +1

Also, WHOA! How did her mom happen to have a urinalysis cup on hand? Now I want to know what kind of drugs what's-her-name has taken before! Can we get a prequel to see her life of sex, drug abuse, and addiction? +1

16. 1:16 Trying to bring sweatbands back. +1

17. 1:17 - 1:19 Why? Just because they found the power coins? That's pretty shady. +1

18. 1:25 - 1:26 I've seen enough trailers to know that her laugh has nothing to do with that moment in the scene, which means we are once again being instructed on when to laugh because advertisers believe the audience is too stupid to recognize humor when they see it. +1

19. 1:28 - 1:30 How do _you_ know? Is there a prophesy? Please tell me there's no prophesy! +1

20. 1:31 - 1:33 Then do it already! +1

21. 1:33 - 1:34 How are the Power Rangers being knocked off of their feet? You'd think that, with their newfound strength,  they would be able to maintain their balance during a tiny Earth-shattering impact like that. +1

22. 1:36 - 1:38 Damn it, Zordon! Why did you bring an abstract idea into an action movie when you know full well that the philosophical discussions of if evil truly exists since it's an abstract idea, what the baseline ideas are of what defines evil, and what requirements need to be met in order to define someone as evil--never mind pure evil--are never going to take place? +1

In fact, I'm going to go ahead and throw in an extra sin. I'm calling it right now: Rita's backstory will either be insufficient or never support her pure evilness status. +1

23. 1:40 - 1:41 Remember how Rita said that she had killed rangers before in the previous trailer? I'll bet she didn't accomplish it like this. +1

24. 1:41 - 1:43 I don't know. With those powers you have now? +1

Alternatively, she seems to have taken a shining to you, as you're the only ranger she's prominently faced in the trailers so far. Why don't you try seducing her? I'd watch that! +1

25. 1:51 - 1:52 Group walking slowly and in line cliché. At least there's no explosion behind them, but the cliché still stands. +1

26. 1:53 Synchronous landing. +1

27. 2:01 - 2:02 How do _you_ know? Is there a prophesy? Please tell me there's no prophesy! +1

Also, protagonist saves loved one from danger cliché. +1

28. 2:10 - 2:11 Damn it, Zordon! Why did you bring an abstract idea into an action movie when you know full well that the philosophical discussions of if time truly exists since it's an abstract idea, if it can be possessed or owned, who can possess or own it, and should it ever be possessed or owned are never going to take place? +1

29. 2:16 Why do they have their faces exposed while in the zords? That is tactically weak. +1

See here's the thing, it'd look like any other passable shitty action movie if it wasn't advertising itself as "power rangers". Nothing in this film remotely looks like power rangers. The megazord looks like a Michael Bay transformer, Rita looks like a rejected Mortal Kombat character, the suits look like Iron Man with tree frog textures, and the individual zords (mastadon, sabertooth, etc) look nothing like the dinosaurs/animals they are meant to represent.

Was the original series cheesy, bad, stupid? Sure, but you can't try banking off nostalgia while simultaneously changing every aspect.

Title: Power Rangers (2017 Movie) Official Trailer – It’s Morphin Time!
Comment:
I had high hopes for this being one of the biggest power rangers fans ever but I have issues with this trailer.

Now don't get me wrong, I love Kanye West and his music and Power is a great song but the marketing people should know that the young men who watched power rangers as a kid who are now grown up are in their mid to late 20s now and are the ones who will go and see this, hate Kanye West so they will take an instant dislike to the trailer.

Why couldn't they use the power ranger series 1 theme tune? It would have been so epic. I also really dislike the liberties they have taken with certain designs like Zordon and Alpha. And why make Rita sexy and scantly clad? It makes no sense.

All I'm saying is, the people who make these movie shouldn't try to rewrite history if they want to make movies like this because the people who go to see them are the people who grew up with the source material. 

Point and case: the last fantastic four movie.
